title: Estonia Employment Change
description: Employment in Estonia decreased by 0.30 in June of 2022. Employment Change in Estonia averaged 0.04 percent from 1995 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 3.50 percent in the fourth quarter of 2021 and a record low of -5.40 percent in the first quarter of 2009. In Estonia, employment change refers to the quarterly change in the number of persons who work for pay or profit, or perform unpaid family work. Estimates include both full-time and part-time employment. This page provides - Estonia Employment Change- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: EUROSTAT
